item.content: Academic Problem: Status - Active, Date Diagnosed - 07/01/2017

tr.td: Goal: Limit Alcohol Consumption, Instructions: Get Sterling to stop drinking so much
Goal: Work on anger issues, Instructions: Sterling is prone to violent "rampage" outbursts. We will work on his need for violence and excitement.
Goal: Maintain Behaviors, Instructions: Follow classroom rules and learn to obey parents.
Goal: Communication Skills, Instructions: I will talk to 1 person each week for 6 months.
Goal: Eating properly, Instructions: Balance meal daily
Goal: Test GOAL GOAL1, Instructions: Test GOAL GOAL1
Goal: GOAL GOAL1, Instructions: GOAL GOAL1
Goal: Test Goal Aman 1, Instructions: Test Goal Aman 1
Goal: Adding in the Note, Instructions: Just adding live in a note12.
Goal: Anger Management, Instructions: Patient Will engage in 1 Positive exercise activity to reduce Anhedonia
Goal: Work on Mommy Issues, Instructions: Sterling has an Oedipal attachment to his mother that affects his other relationships.
Goal: Arriving to work on time, Instructions: Decrease the number of days tardy for work
Goal: Managing Household Budget, Instructions: Establish a monthly household budget for family
Goal: Improve Listening and Comprehension Skills Test, Instructions: Client will work on learning to listen, understand and communicate with others.
